 ^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at| OK, I will start with the minor issues first before discussing various options for bidding this hand and responding to kibber's question. First of all, kia wanted to double my 1@S bid. He is a smidgen light,  as he should have opening points, and he is one point shy. However, because he has no wasted spade points, and has good distribution, a light double here would be reasonable.  dave does not play Bergen raises, so 3@S was fine as a limit raise. One could make a case that he has a strong enough hand to bid 4@S or even bid Jacoby 2NT as QJ of spades are good given I bid spades. And the Q of clubs paired with the K, makes his points actually quite good. |
